page.title: 11NEW HOUSING IN WEST HULL
page.content: A new council estate of 355 houses is being built in West Hull. Some of the houses have people living in them and some are not finished yet. They are built of brick with gas central heating.They have small front and back gardens but no garages. Some of them have a drive. Some of the houses back onto the main Hull to London railway line and these have a patterned gable made by using different coloured bricks. They can be seen by people travelling into Hull.One shows two rugby players, another a ship and another a train. The windows of the houses are incorporated in the design. Most of the houses are 2 or 3 bed- roomed. There are a few 5 bedroomed houses for families of 9 or more.
